👉 Program 1 : Write a Program to print "good morning" and "welcome" continuously on the screen in Java using Threads

CODE :

class Threads extends Thread{
    public void run(){
        for(int i=0 ; i<5 ; i++){
            System.out.println("Good Morning");
        }
    }
}
class Threads2 extends Thread{
    public void run(){
        for(int i=0 ; i<5 ; i++){
            System.out.println("Welcome");
        }
    }
}
public class ThreadPractice {
    public static void main() {
        Threads t1 = new Threads();
        Threads2 t2 = new Threads2();
        t1.start();
        t2.start();
    }
}

OUTPUT :

Good Morning
Welcome
Welcome
Welcome
Welcome
Welcome
Good Morning
Good Morning
Good Morning
Good Morning

Process finished with exit code 0

NOTE : FOR INFINITE PRINT , USE WHILE LOOP IN PLACE OF FOR LOOP...

